  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there any software that counts wifi speed and usage?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several software options available that can monitor and track your WiFi speed and usage. Here are a few popular ones:\n\n1. **GlassWire** (Windows, macOS, Android):\n   - **Features**: Monitors network data usage, provides real-time graphs, and alerts for unusual activities.\n   - **Usage**: Tracks data usage over time and can help identify which applications are using the most bandwidth.\n\n2. **NetLimiter** (Windows):\n   - **Features**: Monitors and limits network traffic, provides real-time bandwidth usage.\n   - **Usage**: Useful for setting data limits and monitoring internet speed for specific applications.\n\n3. **Wireshark** (Windows, macOS, Linux):\n   - **Features**: A powerful network protocol analyzer that captures and displays network traffic in detail.\n   - **Usage**: More technical, useful for in-depth analysis of network performance and usage.\n\n4. **Networx** (Windows):\n   - **Features**: Monitors network usage, provides detailed reports, and sets up alerts for data limits.\n   - **Usage**: Tracks bandwidth usage and can help in managing internet quotas.\n\n5. **BitMeter II** (Windows):\n   - **Features**: Monitors network bandwidth usage and provides historical data.\n   - **Usage**: Simple and effective for tracking internet usage over time.\n\n6. **PRTG Network Monitor** (Windows):\n   - **Features**: Comprehensive network monitoring tool that can track WiFi speed and usage across multiple devices.\n   - **Usage**: Suitable for businesses or larger networks, provides detailed reporting and alerts.\n\n7. **Speedtest.net by Ookla** (Web-based, iOS, Android):\n   - **Features**: Tests internet speed and provides historical data on speed tests.\n   - **Usage**: Quick and easy way to check your current WiFi speed and track it over time.\n\n8. **nPerf** (Web-based, iOS, Android):\n   - **Features**: Tests internet speed, WiFi signal strength, and provides detailed performance reports.\n   - **Usage**: Useful for comparing WiFi performance across different networks and locations.\n\nThese tools vary in complexity and features, so the best choice depends on your specific needs and technical comfort level. For casual home use, tools like GlassWire or Speedtest.net might be sufficient, while more technical users or businesses might prefer Wireshark or PRTG Network Monitor.",
